Class WriterThread

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      controllers.WriterThread
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class WriterThread
extends java.lang.Thread

A writer thread waits until it receives output, and outputs it upon arrival. It periodically checks if there are any broadcast messages available and if so sends them to its output before incrementing its broadcast counter (so each broadcast is only sent once).

Author:
wouterken

run

public void run()
In a loop the thread periodically checks for output and prints it on arrival. it also compares its internal broadcast counter with the global static variable and broadcasts any due messages if these are equal.
